            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced red pepper</strong>,<strong> drained black beans</strong>, <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the pan and stir everything together</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low</p><p>Cook the <strong>basmati rice</strong> for an initial 10 min then add the <strong>browned chicken</strong> (with any juices) and cook for a further 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Mexican-style chicken & black bean pilaf</strong></p>",
